WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.139 --> 00:00:02.749
[Will] <i>Previously on</i>
Will Trent...

2
00:00:02.864 --> 00:00:05.798
Unfortunately. this dark area
right next to it is a tumor.

3
00:00:05.936 --> 00:00:08.716
-What should I do?
-Well. get it out as soon as possible.

4
00:00:08.801 --> 00:00:10.389
[Michael] Faith? I need...

5
00:00:10.527 --> 00:00:12.791
-Hey. Okay. I'm here. I'm here.
-[Michael exclaiming]

6
00:00:12.874 --> 00:00:14.379
[operator]
<i>Sending an ambulance now.</i>

7
00:00:14.462 --> 00:00:16.223
-[gunshot]
-[grunts]

8
00:00:17.189 --> 00:00:18.742
[Will] <i>How bad is it?</i>

9
00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:20.523
[Angie] <i>Her doctor says
the next 48 hours are critical.</i>

10
00:00:20.606 --> 00:00:23.851
[Will] <i>You are my family.
so you need to wake up.</i>

11
00:00:23.989 --> 00:00:26.992
[Amanda] <i>You remember Juice's
defense attorney. James Ulster.</i>

12
00:00:27.441 --> 00:00:29.201
Are you my father?

13
00:00:29.339 --> 00:00:32.052
What kind of a father would
throw his own son into the garbage?

14
00:00:32.135 --> 00:00:34.586
James Ulster. I'm arresting you
for the murders

15
00:00:34.724 --> 00:00:38.348
of Donna Mary Halston
and my mother. Lucy Morales.

16
00:00:38.486 --> 00:00:40.785
Sheriff Caleb Roussard.
I'm Special Agent Will Trent.

17
00:00:40.868 --> 00:00:43.250
[Amanda] Sheriff Caleb Roussard
is your father.

18
00:00:43.388 --> 00:00:46.687
[Angie] <i>You know how I said I grew
up in a group home? Will was there.</i>

19
00:00:46.770 --> 00:00:49.428
-Will. I'm pregnant.
-You're gonna be a mom. Ang.

20
00:00:49.566 --> 00:00:51.554
-A great one.
-[Angie] Thanks for being here.

21
00:00:51.637 --> 00:00:53.777
-Of course.
-Angie? Hey.

22
00:00:53.915 --> 00:00:55.296
-She's okay.
-Okay.

23
00:00:55.434 --> 00:00:57.580
-[Seth] <i>And you're okay?</i>
-[Angie] <i>I'm okay.</i>

24
00:01:01.268 --> 00:01:03.235
[birds chirping]

25
00:01:08.585 --> 00:01:11.312
[dog barking in distance]

26
00:01:17.836 --> 00:01:19.320
[grunts]

27
00:01:22.012 --> 00:01:23.324
[grunts]

28
00:01:24.049 --> 00:01:25.292
[grunts]

29
00:01:29.503 --> 00:01:30.662
[Dr. Roach] <i>How are you doing?</i>

30
00:01:30.745 --> 00:01:33.714
Great. I am great.

31
00:01:33.852 --> 00:01:35.543
Great. That's great.

32
00:01:36.026 --> 00:01:37.200
Yes.

33
00:01:40.514 --> 00:01:42.605
-Can I ask you a question. Dr. Roach?
-Yes.

34
00:01:42.688 --> 00:01:44.331
What does pickleball
have to do with therapy?

35
00:01:44.414 --> 00:01:45.850
Can't we just do this in a nice.

36
00:01:45.933 --> 00:01:47.728
air-conditioned office
like always?

37
00:01:47.866 --> 00:01:50.199
Well. we're keeping your body
busy so your brain is focused

38
00:01:50.282 --> 00:01:53.423
on returning the shot rather
than repressing your feelings.

39
00:01:53.803 --> 00:01:56.654
Won't work. I can repress my
feelings under any circumstances.

40
00:01:56.737 --> 00:01:57.772
How's Angie?

41
00:02:01.742 --> 00:02:03.986
-Still pregnant.
-How do you feel about that?

42
00:02:06.609 --> 00:02:08.611
-A little lost.
-Keep talking.

43
00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:13.063
We've only had each other
for our entire lives.

44
00:02:13.202 --> 00:02:19.000
Now she's moved on to a very
successful. emotionally secure doctor.

45
00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:20.899
and I couldn't be happier
about it.

46
00:02:21.555 --> 00:02:23.177
-Really?
-Yes.

47
00:02:23.315 --> 00:02:26.387
Because it would be
perfectly understandable

48
00:02:26.525 --> 00:02:28.651
for you to have
some mixed feelings about that.

49
00:02:28.734 --> 00:02:32.013
-I do not.
-I mean. if you weren't so scared...

50
00:02:33.049 --> 00:02:36.363
I'm fine! I said I'm fine!
I'm so fine that I'm great!

51
00:02:36.949 --> 00:02:38.296
Nice.

52
00:02:39.607 --> 00:02:42.162
I apologize
for losing my temper.

53
00:02:42.300 --> 00:02:45.372
Don't apologize. Keep it
coming. I'm not scared of you.

54
00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:49.307
I've seen the damage a man's
temper can do in this world.

55
00:02:49.445 --> 00:02:51.481
and I really try
not to go there.

56
00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:53.504
Should we ask the pickleball
how you're doing with that

57
00:02:53.587 --> 00:02:55.148
'cause it's all the way
in Macon?

58
00:02:55.692 --> 00:02:58.912
It's normal for a lot of emotion to
come up when you start therapy.

59
00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:03.286
We talked a lot about your
childhood and the abuse you suffered.

60
00:03:05.115 --> 00:03:08.153
Anger is
an appropriate response.

61
00:03:08.291 --> 00:03:09.416
but it doesn't like
to be ignored.

62
00:03:09.499 --> 00:03:12.847
So if you're mad. be mad.

63
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:14.918
Can we please
just change the subject?

64
00:03:15.505 --> 00:03:16.679
All right.

65
00:03:16.817 --> 00:03:18.715
So. you're going
to Caleb's tonight?

66
00:03:19.164 --> 00:03:21.787
Yeah. I don't know.

67
00:03:23.030 --> 00:03:25.412
His family is loud.

68
00:03:25.550 --> 00:03:26.951
Yeah. some families are loud.

69
00:03:27.034 --> 00:03:28.898
Yeah. and they over salt
their food.

70
00:03:29.036 --> 00:03:32.315
-[gasps] Not the sodium.
-Yeah. and they have an enormous dog.

71
00:03:32.453 --> 00:03:34.593
It's a Great Dane.
It's like a small horse.

72
00:03:34.731 --> 00:03:36.478
I mean. why does anybody
need a dog that big?

73
00:03:36.561 --> 00:03:38.148
What are they compensating for?

74
00:03:38.287 --> 00:03:39.322
[barks]

75
00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:42.553
Maybe you're looking for
reasons for this not to work

76
00:03:42.636 --> 00:03:45.190
because you don't feel worthy
of a family.

77
00:03:45.639 --> 00:03:48.029
You make me out to be
a rather sad man. Dr. Roach.

78
00:03:48.124 --> 00:03:51.714
I'm just saying you have been
surviving on crumbs

79
00:03:51.852 --> 00:03:54.820
and now you have the whole cake.

80
00:03:55.890 --> 00:03:59.963
Yes. but it is a carrot cake
with raisins.

81
00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:03.519
[♪ "Send in the Clowns"
playing]

82
00:04:07.764 --> 00:04:10.733
<i>♪ Isn't it rich ♪</i>

83
00:04:14.426 --> 00:04:17.947
<i>♪ Are we a pair ♪</i>

84
00:04:20.639 --> 00:04:22.785
[Nico] And then he comes into
the living room

85
00:04:22.883 --> 00:04:26.010
while I'm hanging out with a friend.
and he goes... [imitating Will] "New rule.

86
00:04:26.093 --> 00:04:28.426
the soy sauce no longer
needs to be refrigerated.

87
00:04:28.509 --> 00:04:30.511
From now on.
it resides in the pantry."

88
00:04:30.649 --> 00:04:32.237
[chuckles] In the pantry?

89
00:04:32.375 --> 00:04:34.239
-[all laugh]
-[normal voice] I know.

90
00:04:34.377 --> 00:04:37.435
And I'm like. "Okay. do we need to
have a meeting about the ketchup?"

91
00:04:37.518 --> 00:04:38.968
[all laugh]

92
00:04:39.106 --> 00:04:41.936
The man has rules for
his kitchen. I respect that.

93
00:04:42.074 --> 00:04:44.836
This is the best chicken
I've ever had. Mrs. Roussard.

94
00:04:44.974 --> 00:04:47.563
Aw. Nico.
you're welcome back anytime.

95
00:04:47.701 --> 00:04:49.427
Here. Have some more.

96
00:04:49.875 --> 00:04:51.932
-[family member] Pass me the salt.
-[all chattering]

97
00:04:52.015 --> 00:04:55.467
Do you know sharks don't have
any bones? They only have cartilage.

98
00:04:56.537 --> 00:04:58.367
Really?

99
00:04:58.505 --> 00:05:00.734
Did you know shark's eyeballs
are as big as five human eyeballs?

100
00:05:00.817 --> 00:05:03.944
You know. I was just thinking this morning
I don't know anything about sharks.

101
00:05:04.027 --> 00:05:07.734
How about we go look at your book and
you can bring me up to speed on sharks?

102
00:05:08.238 --> 00:05:09.447
Okay.

103
00:05:10.275 --> 00:05:12.173
Pass me the green beans. please.

104
00:05:13.036 --> 00:05:17.593
Now. Reed.
beluga caviar is the best.

105
00:05:17.731 --> 00:05:21.113
However. uh. it has been banned
in the United States

106
00:05:21.251 --> 00:05:25.566
due to the endangered status
of the beluga sturgeon.

107
00:05:25.704 --> 00:05:27.361
[sniffs] Mmm.

108
00:05:27.499 --> 00:05:29.052
[James. Ramston chuckle]

109
00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:31.351
-I like those black truffles we did last time.
-Oh. yes.

110
00:05:31.434 --> 00:05:35.680
Our little. uh. foodie club has
been a highlight of my prison journey.

111
00:05:35.818 --> 00:05:37.525
We sure those fish eggs
travel okay?

112
00:05:37.647 --> 00:05:39.601
-Oh. yes. Yes.
-[prison guard] <i>Lights out. everyone.</i>

113
00:05:39.684 --> 00:05:43.481
Okay. Reed. Now. normally
I serve this on a blini.

114
00:05:43.619 --> 00:05:46.035
-which is like a little crepe.
-What's a crepe?

115
00:05:46.173 --> 00:05:49.487
It's like a little pancake.
Mmm.

116
00:05:49.625 --> 00:05:56.045
But today we must improvise.
so we are using potato chips.

117
00:05:56.183 --> 00:05:58.254
Now. close your eyes. Yeah.

118
00:05:58.392 --> 00:05:59.462
[inhales]

119
00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:01.464
All right. Ah.

120
00:06:01.602 --> 00:06:05.917
Now...
Now feel the texture. mmm?

121
00:06:06.055 --> 00:06:07.056
[Reed] Mmm.

122
00:06:07.712 --> 00:06:10.680
It's like little fishy
boba bubbles only smaller.

123
00:06:10.818 --> 00:06:14.063
-[laughs] Fair. Fair.
-[laughs]

124
00:06:14.201 --> 00:06:18.930
Okay. don't worry. Jerry.
I haven't forgotten about you.

125
00:06:19.068 --> 00:06:22.727
I'm going to make you
the perfect bite.

126
00:06:22.865 --> 00:06:24.867
Oh. Mmm.

127
00:06:25.454 --> 00:06:26.662
[Ramston] Mmm.

128
00:06:27.456 --> 00:06:28.905
[chewing]

129
00:06:29.458 --> 00:06:30.735
[indistinct chatter on PA]

130
00:06:30.873 --> 00:06:32.688
Health care in this country
is so messed up.

131
00:06:32.771 --> 00:06:34.034
Why won't this damn TV come on?

132
00:06:34.117 --> 00:06:35.829
Hey. Franklin.
you need to calm down.

133
00:06:35.912 --> 00:06:37.776
Ormewood is fighting
for his life here.

134
00:06:37.914 --> 00:06:39.502
Running out of time. Franklin.

135
00:06:39.640 --> 00:06:41.435
These could be
his final moments.

136
00:06:41.573 --> 00:06:43.437
Ooh. it came.

137
00:06:43.575 --> 00:06:46.530
[sighs] You look so stupid. I
really can't get over it. [chuckles]

138
00:06:46.613 --> 00:06:48.684
It's for Cooper.
so I don't look sick.

139
00:06:48.822 --> 00:06:50.824
It's working.
Still got his eyelashes.

140
00:06:50.962 --> 00:06:53.620
- [Faith] Mmm. Okay
- [sighs] Come on. man.

141
00:06:54.379 --> 00:06:55.484
[speaking Spanish]

142
00:06:55.622 --> 00:06:57.382
-[Franklin] Oh!
-Oh! There it is.

143
00:06:57.520 --> 00:06:59.349
[TV character speaking Spanish]

144
00:06:59.488 --> 00:07:00.937
It's in Spanish?

145
00:07:01.731 --> 00:07:04.147
Ormewood. this isn't Spanish.

146
00:07:04.285 --> 00:07:05.666
You don't understand this?

147
00:07:05.804 --> 00:07:08.531
Did they leave a little tumor
in there still?

148
00:07:08.669 --> 00:07:10.464
I left a little tumor
in your mom.

149
00:07:10.602 --> 00:07:12.535
[♪ Upbeat music playing]

150
00:07:12.673 --> 00:07:15.020
Okay. close your eyes.

151
00:07:17.367 --> 00:07:18.403
[Ramston] Ah.

152
00:07:18.783 --> 00:07:22.096
Ah. Now describe
what you taste.

153
00:07:22.234 --> 00:07:25.755
It's kind of subtle.
but it's also rich.

154
00:07:26.894 --> 00:07:28.758
I might even use
the word buttery.

155
00:07:29.759 --> 00:07:32.382
I actually like the taste
of the potato chip.

156
00:07:32.521 --> 00:07:37.318
The brightness of the salt really
helps the entire experience. Mmm.

157
00:07:37.698 --> 00:07:39.182
-[James grunts]
-[screams]

158
00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:42.496
-[squelching]
-[Ramston grunts. groans]

159
00:07:42.634 --> 00:07:45.430
-[thuds. strains. groans]
-[squelching]

160
00:07:45.568 --> 00:07:46.776
-Hey!
-[yells]

161
00:07:46.914 --> 00:07:48.537
[grunts]

162
00:07:49.848 --> 00:07:52.092
-[exclaims]
-[thuds. gasps]

163
00:07:53.576 --> 00:07:55.267
[James grunting]

164
00:07:59.271 --> 00:08:00.721
[grunting]

165
00:08:00.859 --> 00:08:03.310
-[breathes heavily]
-[grunting]

166
00:08:03.448 --> 00:08:05.623
<i>♪ Isn't it rich ♪</i>

167
00:08:07.003 --> 00:08:07.836
[grunts]

168
00:08:07.935 --> 00:08:09.799
<i>♪ Isn't it queer ♪</i>

169
00:08:10.420 --> 00:08:11.767
[panting]

170
00:08:15.391 --> 00:08:17.738
It's too late to turn back now.
my boy.

171
00:08:18.152 --> 00:08:20.465
<i>♪ And where are the clowns ♪</i>

172
00:08:20.603 --> 00:08:22.536
I love this green.

173
00:08:22.674 --> 00:08:25.991
I mean. look at it. It's fresh. It's
welcoming. It feels like spring.

174
00:08:26.126 --> 00:08:29.819
I mean. it's... it's...
[exhales]

175
00:08:29.957 --> 00:08:32.339
-You know. it's... it's jubilant.
-[chuckles]

176
00:08:33.029 --> 00:08:34.272
-Jubilant.
-Yeah.

177
00:08:34.410 --> 00:08:35.998
Show me the orange one. bigger.

178
00:08:37.309 --> 00:08:39.484
[chuckles] Okay. bossy.

179
00:08:39.622 --> 00:08:41.072
[laughs]

180
00:08:42.176 --> 00:08:43.212
Uncle Will.

181
00:08:44.109 --> 00:08:45.594
Yes. Calvin?

182
00:08:45.732 --> 00:08:47.927
Don't tell anybody. but
sometimes when I'm in the bathtub.

183
00:08:48.010 --> 00:08:50.426
I get scared a shark
is gonna get me.

184
00:08:51.634 --> 00:08:56.950
Calvin. I promise you. sharks
cannot get you on dry land. okay?

185
00:09:00.505 --> 00:09:03.853
<i>♪ Maybe next year
They'll be here ♪</i>

186
00:09:07.650 --> 00:09:12.724
<i>♪ Maybe next year
They'll be here ♪</i>

187
00:09:14.899 --> 00:09:18.074
<i>♪ Send in the clowns ♪</i>

188
00:09:26.220 --> 00:09:27.325
[♪ music ends]

189
00:09:30.052 --> 00:09:31.384
James Ulster has
a big head start.

190
00:09:31.467 --> 00:09:33.503
What do we know
about this kid he's with?

191
00:09:33.642 --> 00:09:36.562
Reed Hobbs. Single homicide.
Only family he has is his grandmother.

192
00:09:36.645 --> 00:09:38.301
What's Caleb doing here?

193
00:09:38.439 --> 00:09:39.910
Any new information that
comes in comes straight to me

194
00:09:39.993 --> 00:09:42.789
so we can adjust the perimeter.
Okay? Go.

195
00:09:42.927 --> 00:09:44.169
[Will] What's all this?

196
00:09:44.653 --> 00:09:46.986
-I'm running point on the prison break.
-No. you're not.

197
00:09:47.069 --> 00:09:49.367
Prison's in Bradford County.
That's my jurisdiction.

198
00:09:49.450 --> 00:09:52.419
GBI wants me to lead up
the marshals and GDC.

199
00:09:52.557 --> 00:09:54.283
That's absurd.

200
00:09:54.421 --> 00:09:57.397
Will. this is a manhunt. not a
murder that needs to be solved.

201
00:09:58.943 --> 00:10:01.428
You think I don't know
what this man means to you?

202
00:10:01.911 --> 00:10:03.154
I'll find them.

203
00:10:04.189 --> 00:10:05.294
[exhales]

204
00:10:07.330 --> 00:10:09.905
-Deputy Director Appleyard...
-Acting Deputy Director.

205
00:10:09.988 --> 00:10:12.805
Why are we taking a back seat to
the Bradford County Sheriff's Office?

206
00:10:12.888 --> 00:10:15.856
Agent Trent.
you're gonna lower your voice.

207
00:10:15.994 --> 00:10:18.272
-All due respect. but also not really.
-Will.

208
00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:20.847
I think you don't want us
involved in case this goes south

209
00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.491
because you don't wanna look bad

210
00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:24.437
because what you really want
is that deputy director job.

211
00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:27.247
-Will!
-I already have the job. Agent Trent.

212
00:10:27.799 --> 00:10:29.352
Temporarily.

213
00:10:30.802 --> 00:10:33.080
Giving this to Caleb
was my idea.

214
00:10:33.218 --> 00:10:34.185
Amanda.

215
00:10:34.323 --> 00:10:35.255
Should you be here?

216
00:10:35.393 --> 00:10:36.601
Probably not.

217
00:10:37.222 --> 00:10:39.949
But I came to give Bill
my opinion on this case.

218
00:10:40.087 --> 00:10:43.387
So. are you telling me you got out of
bed and hobbled over here with your cane

219
00:10:43.470 --> 00:10:44.816
to put me on the bench?

220
00:10:44.954 --> 00:10:47.439
Yes. I did.
You're too close to this. Will.

221
00:10:47.577 --> 00:10:50.428
Oh. okay. Well then. I guess. you
know. I'll just go take a bubble bath

222
00:10:50.511 --> 00:10:53.017
-and wait for James Ulster to kill somebody else.
-Okay. Let's go.

223
00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:55.171
This behavior
is proving my point!

224
00:10:55.309 --> 00:10:57.650
It's insane that you would
take me off this case.

225
00:10:57.760 --> 00:11:00.832
I know Ulster better than any
of you or Sheriff Roussard.

226
00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:03.490
This man killed my mother
and left me to die.

227
00:11:04.077 --> 00:11:07.238
So on behalf of the state of Georgia.
I would just like to say thank you both

228
00:11:07.321 --> 00:11:10.877
-for your terrible judgment.
-Oh. my God. Will. come on.

229
00:11:11.498 --> 00:11:12.430
Go.

230
00:11:12.568 --> 00:11:13.914
[breathes heavily]

231
00:11:14.604 --> 00:11:17.663
I consider this a complete and total
undermining of me by Amanda Wagner.

232
00:11:17.746 --> 00:11:19.941
Let the marshals do the
roadblocks and watch the busses.

233
00:11:20.024 --> 00:11:21.404
We can still investigate.

234
00:11:22.095 --> 00:11:23.717
Wait. was this always here?

235
00:11:26.271 --> 00:11:28.446
-You can't knock?
-I got a project for you.

236
00:11:28.584 --> 00:11:30.537
Ormewood. why are you in
this tiny dark closet?

237
00:11:30.620 --> 00:11:32.988
This is my office. okay? They
gave me this new computer job.

238
00:11:33.071 --> 00:11:35.025
and I can't do it
unless I have peace and quiet.

239
00:11:35.108 --> 00:11:36.730
-What do you need?
-It's Ulster.

240
00:11:36.868 --> 00:11:38.200
We need to figure out
where he's going.

241
00:11:38.283 --> 00:11:40.381
I thought you guys
got thrown off that case.

242
00:11:40.492 --> 00:11:42.515
-How'd you know that?
-It's on the WhatsApp chain.

243
00:11:42.598 --> 00:11:45.483
We're working the case on the
DL. which is why we're using you.

244
00:11:45.566 --> 00:11:47.589
We know that Ulster is
well connected and charming.

245
00:11:47.672 --> 00:11:49.626
It's possible that
he's using people to help him.

246
00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:50.696
and we want to know who.

247
00:11:50.779 --> 00:11:52.712
Morning. Snack time.

248
00:11:52.850 --> 00:11:54.801
It's not vending machine hours.
Franklin.

249
00:11:54.886 --> 00:11:57.233
You made that up. Ormy.
No such thing.

250
00:11:57.371 --> 00:12:00.650
No. you don't fit inside of
here. okay? Absolutely not.

251
00:12:00.789 --> 00:12:02.100
Discrimination.

252
00:12:02.238 --> 00:12:04.033
Will. hi.

253
00:12:04.171 --> 00:12:06.401
You think four armed officers stationed
at my place is a little excessive?

254
00:12:06.484 --> 00:12:07.865
No. I do not.

255
00:12:08.003 --> 00:12:09.438
James Ulster abducted you
from my home last time.

256
00:12:09.521 --> 00:12:11.578
so it makes perfect sense
to give you protection.

257
00:12:11.661 --> 00:12:13.822
I can also come over and sleep
on the couch if that's better for you.

258
00:12:13.905 --> 00:12:15.907
No?
Then four armed guards it is.

259
00:12:16.045 --> 00:12:17.875
So. uh.
what are we all doing in here?

260
00:12:18.392 --> 00:12:20.104
It's 'cause you got kicked
off the Ulster manhunt.

261
00:12:20.187 --> 00:12:21.588
-I saw it on the WhatsApp.
-Yeah.

262
00:12:21.671 --> 00:12:23.418
What's everyone talking about?
What is this?

263
00:12:23.501 --> 00:12:24.951
APD-GBI gossip.

264
00:12:25.089 --> 00:12:26.987
It's a group chat everyone's on.

265
00:12:27.125 --> 00:12:28.506
Oh. you're not on it?

266
00:12:29.679 --> 00:12:31.336
-Are you on it?
-Yes.

267
00:12:32.027 --> 00:12:34.167
-Okay. I feel like yelling again.
-Okay.

268
00:12:34.305 --> 00:12:37.018
Ormewood. can you just pull all of James
Ulster's clients as far back as you can?

269
00:12:37.101 --> 00:12:40.449
Yes. and also pull all of his
visitor logs from the prison.

270
00:12:40.587 --> 00:12:41.864
Same goes for Reed Hobbs.

271
00:12:42.002 --> 00:12:43.590
I know how to do that now.

272
00:12:43.728 --> 00:12:46.096
That's gonna be a long list.
What are you gonna do with it?

273
00:12:46.179 --> 00:12:49.389
We're gonna cold call.
and it's gonna suck.

274
00:12:51.080 --> 00:12:52.841
[Will] James Ulster.

275
00:12:52.979 --> 00:12:56.534
He defended you on a money
laundering charge back in 2006.

276
00:12:56.672 --> 00:12:58.487
As you probably know.
he escaped from prison.

277
00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:01.504
We saw that he defended you
on a DUI ten years ago.

278
00:13:01.642 --> 00:13:04.818
No. ma'am. I can assure you
this is not a scam.

279
00:13:04.956 --> 00:13:06.544
Several DUIs?

280
00:13:06.682 --> 00:13:08.235
I see that now. Quite a few.

281
00:13:08.373 --> 00:13:09.616
I'm not a robot.

282
00:13:09.754 --> 00:13:11.535
Okay. can you let us know
if you hear from him?

283
00:13:11.618 --> 00:13:14.690
And maybe consider a
12-step program too. Good night.

284
00:13:14.828 --> 00:13:16.036
[phone beeps]

285
00:13:18.004 --> 00:13:20.178
Do I sound like a robot?

286
00:13:21.179 --> 00:13:22.836
-Pizza?
-No.

287
00:13:22.974 --> 00:13:24.306
You know. I hate that window.

288
00:13:24.389 --> 00:13:25.528
[Faith] Mmm.

289
00:13:25.666 --> 00:13:27.715
It kind of sounds like
you need some pizza.

290
00:13:28.566 --> 00:13:31.155
Seriously.
do I sound like a robot?

291
00:13:31.638 --> 00:13:33.502
Okay. Sometimes.

292
00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:35.455
when you're not screaming like a
lunatic at the guy who signs your checks.

293
00:13:35.538 --> 00:13:37.368
I don't care.
That guy's an asshole.

294
00:13:37.506 --> 00:13:39.025
Who? Appleyard?

295
00:13:39.163 --> 00:13:43.546
Yeah. I prefer Amanda
and she's terrifying.

296
00:13:43.684 --> 00:13:45.845
Wait. what are you still
doing here? It's 3:00 a.m.

297
00:13:45.928 --> 00:13:49.021
Well. Gina has the kids and I'm
trying not to feel like a useless turd.

298
00:13:49.104 --> 00:13:50.436
Well. you came to
the wrong place.

299
00:13:50.519 --> 00:13:52.590
This is useless turd
headquarters.

300
00:13:52.728 --> 00:13:54.094
What is that? No more names.

301
00:13:54.212 --> 00:13:56.007
Ooh. do the elevator thing.

302
00:13:56.145 --> 00:13:57.629
[chuckles]

303
00:13:58.492 --> 00:14:01.564
Hey. good work today. Mitchell.
I'll see you at home. okay?

304
00:14:01.702 --> 00:14:03.068
Mitchell. just come in here.

305
00:14:04.050 --> 00:14:08.917
And yes. these are more names.
and I would start with this one.

306
00:14:09.572 --> 00:14:11.126
Sal Moreno.

307
00:14:11.264 --> 00:14:12.941
Ulster got him off a rape
charge involving his babysitter.

308
00:14:13.024 --> 00:14:14.460
but they kept in touch
over the years.

309
00:14:14.543 --> 00:14:16.441
What makes this guy so special?

310
00:14:16.579 --> 00:14:19.359
Because this guy owns a steak
house inside the roadblocks.

311
00:14:19.720 --> 00:14:21.136
Let me see that.

312
00:14:25.795 --> 00:14:27.245
[James] Mmm.

313
00:14:28.315 --> 00:14:29.627
Mmm.

314
00:14:31.249 --> 00:14:34.045
Feeling better. Reed? Hmm?

315
00:14:34.494 --> 00:14:37.669
-Protein. It's good for you.
-[phone rings]

316
00:14:40.431 --> 00:14:41.466
Hmm.

317
00:14:42.536 --> 00:14:43.572
Mmm.

318
00:14:51.614 --> 00:14:53.409
[ringing continues]

319
00:14:55.825 --> 00:14:58.483
Special Agent Will Trent.

320
00:14:59.795 --> 00:15:01.555
[exclaims] I knew it. See?

321
00:15:01.693 --> 00:15:03.212
Good guess. Hello. James.

322
00:15:03.350 --> 00:15:04.862
Mmm.
No. it wasn't a guess. I...

323
00:15:05.318 --> 00:15:09.149
I knew you'd figure it out just
a little faster than I'd hoped.

324
00:15:09.287 --> 00:15:10.875
but I'm proud of you.

325
00:15:11.013 --> 00:15:14.534
<i>I know you found your shiny.
new biological father.</i>

326
00:15:14.672 --> 00:15:16.672
I need a location
on the following number.

327
00:15:16.916 --> 00:15:18.434
You'll always be my boy.

328
00:15:18.572 --> 00:15:20.975
Oh. you sound. uh. threatened.
Maybe a little jealous.

329
00:15:21.058 --> 00:15:23.715
Why don't you come on in?
We can discuss it in person.

330
00:15:23.853 --> 00:15:26.373
No. no. no. no. no can do.

331
00:15:26.511 --> 00:15:29.894
You would not believe
the day I'm having.

332
00:15:30.481 --> 00:15:33.933
I need a drive-by wellness check on
a Sal Moreno. Last known address...

333
00:15:34.071 --> 00:15:36.245
A bit of a mess here.

334
00:15:36.383 --> 00:15:38.454
You didn't hurt anyone.
did you. James?

335
00:15:38.592 --> 00:15:40.494
[James whispering]
Oh. no. it wasn't me.

336
00:15:40.594 --> 00:15:43.011
Not to throw anyone
under the bus. but. uh...

337
00:15:43.149 --> 00:15:46.221
[normal voice] ...when you
choose your family in prison.

338
00:15:46.359 --> 00:15:48.671
-it is slim pickings...
-[finger snaps]

339
00:15:48.809 --> 00:15:52.330
[James] <i>...even though...
I'm very fond of my Reed.</i>

340
00:15:53.159 --> 00:15:54.988
Did Reed kill somebody?

341
00:15:55.126 --> 00:15:58.405
He's just a kid full of passion.
vibrance. When did we lose that?

342
00:15:58.543 --> 00:16:00.890
Anyway. Glad to reconnect. hmm.

343
00:16:01.029 --> 00:16:02.637
Oh. same.
You know. I miss you too.

344
00:16:02.720 --> 00:16:04.259
How about we stay on the phone
and have a proper catch-up?

345
00:16:04.342 --> 00:16:05.709
-It's been a while.
-[James] <i>No.</i>

346
00:16:05.792 --> 00:16:08.415
[finger snaps] Gotta go.
Gotta go. [clears throat]

347
00:16:08.553 --> 00:16:11.315
And. Will.
I just want my freedom.

348
00:16:11.453 --> 00:16:13.041
I'm not coming after you.

349
00:16:13.662 --> 00:16:17.769
It would be so great
if you could return the favor.

350
00:16:17.907 --> 00:16:18.978
No can do.

351
00:16:19.116 --> 00:16:20.289
Hmm.

352
00:16:20.427 --> 00:16:23.534
So be it. Catch me if you can.

353
00:16:29.264 --> 00:16:31.507
[♪ "A Little Closer" playing]

354
00:16:38.549 --> 00:16:41.207
-Okay. avocado toast...
-Aw.

355
00:16:41.345 --> 00:16:42.332
...when you're ready for it.

356
00:16:42.415 --> 00:16:44.279
Well. you and Eleanor.

357
00:16:44.417 --> 00:16:48.559
No. no Eleanor. I had an Eleanor.
Ex-boyfriend set her on fire.

358
00:16:48.697 --> 00:16:50.650
[sucks teeth] All right.
well. strike Eleanor then.

359
00:16:50.733 --> 00:16:52.494
Yeah. but thank you
for breakfast.

360
00:16:52.632 --> 00:16:53.978
-I appreciate it...
-Yep.

361
00:16:54.116 --> 00:16:56.222
...as does Lola.

362
00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.671
Mmm. I had a Lola.

363
00:16:57.809 --> 00:16:59.915
Died in a motorcycle accident
on I-85.

364
00:17:00.053 --> 00:17:01.903
-[Angie] Oh.
-She didn't have any skin left.

365
00:17:01.986 --> 00:17:04.851
-Oh. Search continues.
-The search continues.

366
00:17:04.989 --> 00:17:08.027
Don't worry. we will find it.
I love you.

367
00:17:12.203 --> 00:17:14.240
What is this?
What am I looking at?

368
00:17:14.378 --> 00:17:16.794
-You're looking at a box.
-What's in the box?

369
00:17:16.932 --> 00:17:18.678
-You will find a ring in the box.
-Are you insane?

370
00:17:18.761 --> 00:17:20.335
-Why are you... Stop yelling at me.
-Like. why...

371
00:17:20.418 --> 00:17:23.387
I am trying to ask you
to marry me right now.

372
00:17:25.147 --> 00:17:26.769
You make me laugh.

373
00:17:26.907 --> 00:17:28.909
You're the bravest woman
I've ever met.

374
00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:32.258
You make me feel more alive
than I have in years.

375
00:17:32.396 --> 00:17:34.039
But most importantly.
you're super hot.

376
00:17:34.122 --> 00:17:35.088
[giggles]

377
00:17:35.226 --> 00:17:37.849
[breathing heavily]

378
00:17:41.508 --> 00:17:44.753
-Holy cow. Jeez.
-You like it?

379
00:17:44.891 --> 00:17:48.067
Yeah. but I can't wear that
at work.

380
00:17:48.205 --> 00:17:52.243
I know. That's why I got you
this super boring backup.

381
00:17:53.106 --> 00:17:54.452
[Angie whispering] Oh.

382
00:17:55.315 --> 00:17:56.535
That's really pretty too.

383
00:17:57.248 --> 00:18:00.872
-Is that a yes?
-You got me two rings. That is so...

384
00:18:01.010 --> 00:18:02.529
Ang. I'm dying over here.

385
00:18:04.393 --> 00:18:07.776
-Yeah. Yes. yes.
-Yeah?

386
00:18:08.673 --> 00:18:09.571
Yes.

387
00:18:09.709 --> 00:18:12.263
[♪ "A Little Closer" continues]

388
00:18:15.473 --> 00:18:16.888
[♪ Music ends]

389
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:24.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

390
00:18:27.382 --> 00:18:29.232
The marshals are less
than five minutes away.

391
00:18:29.315 --> 00:18:31.662
That thing you do.
you better do it fast.

392
00:18:32.352 --> 00:18:34.354
[♪ "Vitamin C" playing]

393
00:18:38.082 --> 00:18:42.466
<i>♪ Her daddy
Got a big aeroplane ♪</i>

394
00:18:42.604 --> 00:18:46.401
<i>♪ Her mommy holds
All the family cash ♪</i>

395
00:18:46.539 --> 00:18:50.336
<i>♪ A beautiful rose
Stay at the corner ♪</i>

396
00:18:50.784 --> 00:18:54.823
<i>♪ She is living
In and out of tune ♪</i>

397
00:19:02.693 --> 00:19:04.108
He was looking for something.

398
00:19:05.005 --> 00:19:06.455
He didn't find it.

399
00:19:06.593 --> 00:19:07.994
<i>♪ You're losing
Your vitamin... ♪</i>

400
00:19:08.077 --> 00:19:10.079
How you breathe in this suit?

401
00:19:10.770 --> 00:19:12.461
No wonder you're so uptight.

402
00:19:12.599 --> 00:19:15.706
Where did you get this.
Ross Repressed For Less?

403
00:19:16.258 --> 00:19:17.777
[Will] Mmm.

404
00:19:20.193 --> 00:19:21.677
Someone entered.

405
00:19:23.058 --> 00:19:24.301
<i>♪ Hey. you ♪</i>

406
00:19:24.749 --> 00:19:27.821
[Will] <i>He startled Reed.
He was armed.</i>

407
00:19:27.959 --> 00:19:29.858
<i>♪ You're losing
You're losing ♪</i>

408
00:19:29.996 --> 00:19:31.052
[Will] <i>Reed took his gun.</i>

409
00:19:31.135 --> 00:19:32.826
<i>♪ Your vitamin C ♪</i>

410
00:19:53.295 --> 00:19:56.229
How's it going with daddy?
By the way. I'd love to meet him.

411
00:19:56.367 --> 00:19:58.783
[huffs] I'm sure you would.

412
00:19:59.439 --> 00:20:01.372
He is a bit of a cliche though. right?

413
00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:03.788
I mean. the cowboy hat.
the boots.

414
00:20:03.926 --> 00:20:06.225
You murdered sex workers
and sewed their mouths shut.

415
00:20:06.308 --> 00:20:09.311
-I think I can live with his cowboy hat.
-Hmm.

416
00:20:13.453 --> 00:20:17.595
[distorted shattering]

417
00:20:18.044 --> 00:20:19.390
[distorted grunting]

418
00:20:19.528 --> 00:20:21.634
<i>♪ You're losing
Your vitamin C ♪</i>

419
00:20:22.704 --> 00:20:24.637
Yeah. I did. I did do that.

420
00:20:24.775 --> 00:20:28.744
but I used to bring my reusable cup
to Starbucks. so let God be the judge.

421
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:30.643
Get out of my head. James.

422
00:20:31.333 --> 00:20:33.611
[distorted dialogue]

423
00:20:34.957 --> 00:20:36.407
[distorted screaming]

424
00:20:37.270 --> 00:20:40.584
After killing one patron.
he decided to kill 'em all.

425
00:20:41.032 --> 00:20:42.241
[screams]

426
00:20:42.379 --> 00:20:43.311
[grunts]

427
00:20:43.449 --> 00:20:44.795
In for a penny.

428
00:20:45.451 --> 00:20:48.316
My point is.
he's not like you and me.

429
00:20:48.454 --> 00:20:50.559
There is no you and me.

430
00:20:50.697 --> 00:20:52.551
[Reed] Guys.
are we doing this or what?

431
00:20:53.044 --> 00:20:56.876
Yes. Fine.
[sucks teeth] Go ahead.

432
00:20:57.946 --> 00:20:59.292
[distorted grunt]

433
00:20:59.430 --> 00:21:01.694
-[Reed] What's in that. Sal?
-He questioned the owner.

434
00:21:01.777 --> 00:21:05.781
I don't know. I don't know
what you're talking about.

435
00:21:07.921 --> 00:21:08.853
Oof.

436
00:21:08.991 --> 00:21:11.270
Cold-blooded. Hmm.

437
00:21:25.076 --> 00:21:27.044
Where were you
during all this. James?

438
00:21:28.908 --> 00:21:31.911
Reed Hobbs was a 16-year-old
when he held up a gas station.

439
00:21:32.049 --> 00:21:34.465
The clerk pulled the gun
and Reed shot him.

440
00:21:36.122 --> 00:21:37.468
Killers gonna kill.

441
00:21:38.918 --> 00:21:39.781
Sure.

442
00:21:40.333 --> 00:21:44.579
Unless he was just a kid
who made a terrible mistake.

443
00:21:44.993 --> 00:21:47.513
I think when I send this
back to the lab.

444
00:21:47.651 --> 00:21:52.311
this tissue is gonna test high for
saline and match Reed Hobbs's DNA.

445
00:21:54.347 --> 00:21:55.969
It was you.

446
00:21:56.107 --> 00:21:58.717
I didn't think it was because
you like to savor your kills.

447
00:21:58.800 --> 00:22:01.754
But I guess you were frustrated
things weren't going according to plan.

448
00:22:01.837 --> 00:22:03.632
[♪ Suspenseful music plays]

449
00:22:03.770 --> 00:22:06.000
-[Will] <i>You were looking for something.</i>
-[grunts]

450
00:22:06.083 --> 00:22:07.395
[patrons scream]

451
00:22:07.533 --> 00:22:09.383
-[patron] Oh. my God.
-[Reed] Don't. Wait.

452
00:22:09.466 --> 00:22:12.089
-[patron grunts]
-[grunting]

453
00:22:13.435 --> 00:22:14.712
[Will] <i>You didn't find it.</i>

454
00:22:16.507 --> 00:22:19.372
[Sal crying] No. please. No.

455
00:22:20.062 --> 00:22:22.050
[Will] You killed everyone
in that restaurant

456
00:22:22.133 --> 00:22:24.846
while poor Reed cried by the
table waiting for it to be over.

457
00:22:24.929 --> 00:22:26.966
But you brought him
a soft drink.

458
00:22:27.104 --> 00:22:29.575
thought that'd make him feel
better about the room full of corpses.

459
00:22:29.658 --> 00:22:31.798
Okay. you got me.

460
00:22:31.936 --> 00:22:33.731
But what I find interesting

461
00:22:33.869 --> 00:22:38.046
is that I'm still wearing...
[chuckles] ...the suit.

462
00:22:38.184 --> 00:22:41.325
which makes me think you're
living vicariously through me.

463
00:22:41.463 --> 00:22:43.327
[huffs] Shut up. James.

464
00:22:43.465 --> 00:22:46.641
[James] Uh. just throwing it
out there. You got some anger.

465
00:22:46.779 --> 00:22:48.145
I wish you could do
something about it.

466
00:22:48.228 --> 00:22:51.093
Have you ever considered
murdering sex workers?

467
00:22:51.231 --> 00:22:52.612
You don't know me.

468
00:22:52.750 --> 00:22:53.979
You actually think
that suit is fooling anyone?

469
00:22:54.062 --> 00:22:55.028
I said shut it.

470
00:22:55.166 --> 00:22:57.237
You think people
can't tell what you are?

471
00:22:57.376 --> 00:23:00.054
You're a monster and I'd put
the needle in you myself if I could.

472
00:23:00.137 --> 00:23:03.934
You're just a scared. abused
little boy who can't read.

473
00:23:04.072 --> 00:23:06.315
Get out of my head!

474
00:23:06.454 --> 00:23:08.387
-[Faith] Will!
-[gasps]

475
00:23:10.423 --> 00:23:11.804
You okay?

476
00:23:15.808 --> 00:23:18.296
It was Ulster who killed
all these people. not Reed.

477
00:23:18.431 --> 00:23:19.556
He was looking for something.

478
00:23:19.639 --> 00:23:21.330
Yeah. it was probably this.

479
00:23:21.469 --> 00:23:24.181
It's ten grand and two fake
passports for Ulster and Reed.

480
00:23:24.264 --> 00:23:25.727
A courier just dropped it off.

481
00:23:26.508 --> 00:23:28.669
-Well. he was a little late.
-He was a little high.

482
00:23:28.752 --> 00:23:31.045
An anonymous client
hired him to put the package

483
00:23:31.168 --> 00:23:33.607
behind the paper towel
dispenser in the men's room.

484
00:23:33.860 --> 00:23:35.607
Passports means he was trying
to get out of the country.

485
00:23:35.690 --> 00:23:38.106
-but now he's scrambling.
-Mm-hmm.

486
00:23:38.244 --> 00:23:40.094
There should be six cars
out in that parking lot.

487
00:23:40.177 --> 00:23:41.558
They're only four.

488
00:23:41.696 --> 00:23:43.235
They split up.
Is Caleb here yet?

489
00:23:43.318 --> 00:23:44.595
-No.
-Good.

490
00:23:44.733 --> 00:23:46.597
Reed Hobbs is scared.

491
00:23:46.735 --> 00:23:47.895
I think he didn't know
how violent

492
00:23:47.978 --> 00:23:49.980
-Ulster would get.
-[siren wailing]

493
00:23:50.739 --> 00:23:52.451
Maybe he's gone to see
someone familiar.

494
00:23:52.534 --> 00:23:54.053
His grandma.

495
00:23:56.676 --> 00:23:58.008
[Franklin]
<i>What else are you craving?</i>

496
00:23:58.091 --> 00:24:00.577
[Angie] Just. like.
olives and salty things.

497
00:24:00.715 --> 00:24:02.737
You know what though. my
egg allergy just disappeared.

498
00:24:02.820 --> 00:24:05.098
-Shut up. For real?
-Yeah. Mm-hmm.

499
00:24:05.236 --> 00:24:08.688
Guys. I found something
and it's magnificent!

500
00:24:08.826 --> 00:24:12.727
I'd like you to meet...
Janice-Theresa Weggle.

501
00:24:13.555 --> 00:24:16.834
Uh. Polaski. get that Chinese
food out of here. I'm gonna hurl.

502
00:24:16.972 --> 00:24:19.557
-Today's my nauseous day. Please.
-Okay. okay. okay.

503
00:24:19.941 --> 00:24:21.598
So. why do I care
about a Janice?

504
00:24:21.736 --> 00:24:23.979
Janice-Theresa.
There's a hyphen.

505
00:24:24.117 --> 00:24:25.981
And I will let her
tell you the rest.

506
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:31.331
<i>Hey. y'all. Come get ready with
me to visit my fiance in prison.</i>

507
00:24:31.470 --> 00:24:33.023
-Uh-oh.
-[shushes]

508
00:24:33.161 --> 00:24:35.439
<i>Okay. I want to start
with a modest top. right?</i>

509
00:24:35.577 --> 00:24:37.855
<i>-And... Yep.</i>
-Oh. girl. [scoffs]

510
00:24:37.993 --> 00:24:42.204
<i>And then. I like to complete
my look with a big bold red lip.</i>

511
00:24:42.342 --> 00:24:46.243
<i>Just like this. y'all.
Because my fiance is a lip man.</i>

512
00:24:46.381 --> 00:24:48.210
<i>Lips and nails...</i>

513
00:24:48.348 --> 00:24:50.026
[mouthing words] <i>-...lips
and nails. -that's what he's into.</i>

514
00:24:50.109 --> 00:24:51.614
<i>And so. it's important
for me to look nice.</i>

515
00:24:51.697 --> 00:24:53.258
<i>I'd give him my life if I could.</i>

516
00:24:53.388 --> 00:24:54.996
<i>-I just...</i>[squeals]
-Okay. here it comes.

517
00:24:55.079 --> 00:24:58.462
<i>I cannot wait to be
Mrs. James Ulster.</i>

518
00:24:58.600 --> 00:25:00.464
-Yes!
-No way. Girl...

519
00:25:00.602 --> 00:25:02.293
Come on.

520
00:25:02.880 --> 00:25:04.468
-Let's get her.
-Let's go.

521
00:25:04.606 --> 00:25:06.801
<i>-And I like to be hot and sweaty.</i>
-Well done.

522
00:25:08.472 --> 00:25:09.784
[Angie sighs]

523
00:25:09.922 --> 00:25:12.234
Is this lady ever gonna show up?

524
00:25:12.787 --> 00:25:16.515
Maybe she's already in the
Bahamas waiting for her man to arrive.

525
00:25:18.378 --> 00:25:20.815
What possesses someone to
want to marry a serial killer?

526
00:25:20.898 --> 00:25:22.728
Mmm. Desperation. loneliness.

527
00:25:22.866 --> 00:25:24.661
[Michael]
Real romantic. Franklin.

528
00:25:24.799 --> 00:25:27.111
How about
an unwavering belief in love?

529
00:25:28.872 --> 00:25:29.804
Who are you?

530
00:25:29.942 --> 00:25:31.875
I don't know. man.

531
00:25:32.013 --> 00:25:35.416
Ever since I got sick. I've been moved
by people and their stupid feelings.

532
00:25:35.499 --> 00:25:38.523
She wanted a connection. It
was the best option she could find.

533
00:25:38.606 --> 00:25:40.090
Are you okay?

534
00:25:40.228 --> 00:25:42.667
My nauseous day is also
sometimes my emotional day.

535
00:25:42.886 --> 00:25:44.819
I probably shouldn't
have come here.

536
00:25:44.957 --> 00:25:47.393
I'm gonna close my eyes for a few
seconds. Tell me when she shows up. yeah?

537
00:25:47.476 --> 00:25:48.926
-Noted.
-Okay.

538
00:25:52.585 --> 00:25:56.244
Angela Agnes Bernadette
Polaski. are you engaged?

539
00:25:56.382 --> 00:25:58.177
[gasps. exclaims]

540
00:25:58.315 --> 00:26:00.579
Speaking of an unwavering
belief in love. let me see the ring.

541
00:26:00.662 --> 00:26:02.146
[Michael. Franklin] Oh!

542
00:26:02.284 --> 00:26:03.582
-Congrats. Polaski. You bagged a doctor?
-Ah!

543
00:26:03.665 --> 00:26:05.667
-Yeah.
-Ooh!

544
00:26:05.805 --> 00:26:07.413
Make sure you tell him to invite all of
his gay doctor friends to the wedding.

545
00:26:07.496 --> 00:26:08.725
Look at all these diamonds.

546
00:26:08.808 --> 00:26:10.603
I know.
it's kind of a lot. right?

547
00:26:10.741 --> 00:26:12.522
Well. like. he gave me another
one. but I kinda like this one.

548
00:26:12.605 --> 00:26:15.401
No. no. no. Hey. no. No. Do
not put that on the WhatsApp.

549
00:26:15.539 --> 00:26:18.024
-Come on. this is breaking news!
-No!

550
00:26:18.162 --> 00:26:19.716
[groans]

551
00:26:20.440 --> 00:26:21.649
[sighs]

552
00:26:22.028 --> 00:26:23.685
Will doesn't know yet?

553
00:26:25.031 --> 00:26:28.069
-Not yet.
-Oh. man. He's gonna be crushed.

554
00:26:28.897 --> 00:26:30.830
-Can I tell him?
-Absolutely not.

555
00:26:30.968 --> 00:26:33.143
You feeling a little
conflicted. preggy?

556
00:26:33.281 --> 00:26:35.076
No. just...

557
00:26:36.871 --> 00:26:37.996
All right. stakeout rules apply?

558
00:26:38.079 --> 00:26:39.494
Nothing leaves this car.

559
00:26:39.632 --> 00:26:40.875
Car is sacred.

560
00:26:43.360 --> 00:26:44.430
Okay.

561
00:26:44.948 --> 00:26:47.675
God. I love Seth. He's...

562
00:26:48.607 --> 00:26:50.367
He's so good to me.

563
00:26:51.748 --> 00:26:53.211
You know. when he looks at me.

564
00:26:53.301 --> 00:26:56.925
I don't see all the mistakes
I made looking back.

565
00:26:57.477 --> 00:27:00.239
But sometimes I think
about the universe where...

566
00:27:01.896 --> 00:27:03.173
it's Will.

567
00:27:04.243 --> 00:27:07.266
I don't know what that means.
and I feel really guilty about it.

568
00:27:07.349 --> 00:27:09.739
'Cause you're beating
yourself up for being human.

569
00:27:10.939 --> 00:27:13.217
Oh. look.
there's Janice-Theresa.

570
00:27:13.355 --> 00:27:14.943
-Hey.
-Where?

571
00:27:15.841 --> 00:27:17.636
Oh. God. Look at this lady.

572
00:27:17.774 --> 00:27:22.054
Yeah. look at her. Polaski.
She's engaged to a serial killer.

573
00:27:22.192 --> 00:27:23.938
Do you think that
she's beating herself up?

574
00:27:24.021 --> 00:27:25.471
-She is not.
-Mm-mmm.

575
00:27:25.609 --> 00:27:27.597
She just goes to Kroger.
buys a low-fat cottage cheese.

576
00:27:27.680 --> 00:27:31.477
her Chardonnay and her modest
tops. And goes about her life.

577
00:27:31.615 --> 00:27:32.616
[engine revs]

578
00:27:32.754 --> 00:27:34.618
-Whoa!
-[screams]

579
00:27:34.756 --> 00:27:36.240
[all] Oh.

580
00:27:36.378 --> 00:27:38.608
-Uh. you just hit my mailbox!
-Oh. that was on purpose.

581
00:27:38.691 --> 00:27:41.266
-[woman] Screw that mailbox. Hey. bitch.
-Wait. do they know each other?

582
00:27:41.349 --> 00:27:42.957
-What?
-[woman] You've been lying.

583
00:27:43.040 --> 00:27:44.476
-I don't know you.
-You don't have to know me.

584
00:27:44.559 --> 00:27:46.064
-I don't know you!
-Don't you throw that at me!

585
00:27:46.147 --> 00:27:47.306
-She threw her with that.
-I don't know you!

586
00:27:47.389 --> 00:27:48.722
-You're gonna know me...
-Bread.

587
00:27:48.805 --> 00:27:50.427
...'cause you're a liar.

588
00:27:50.565 --> 00:27:52.311
-Come on. Let's go.
-No. no. Hold on. It's getting good.

589
00:27:52.394 --> 00:27:53.347
-Come on.
-Come on.

590
00:27:53.430 --> 00:27:54.880
[woman screams]

591
00:27:55.018 --> 00:27:57.213
-[Janice-Theresa] Oh. my God.
-Girl. she can run.

592
00:27:57.296 --> 00:27:58.884
-[woman grunts]
-[all] Oh!

593
00:27:59.022 --> 00:28:00.354
Okay. I feel like
we should call it.

594
00:28:00.437 --> 00:28:02.080
Just wanna see how it play out.
Come on.

595
00:28:02.163 --> 00:28:03.840
-[Janice-Theresa grunts]
-Oh. not the car!

596
00:28:03.923 --> 00:28:07.651
-[grunting]
-You are not his fiancee! I am!

597
00:28:07.789 --> 00:28:09.170
He's mine!

598
00:28:09.308 --> 00:28:11.399
Two fiances. One serial killer.
two fiancees.

599
00:28:11.482 --> 00:28:12.849
-[Janice-Theresa] Get off!
-[Michael] I love my job.

600
00:28:12.932 --> 00:28:14.299
-[all] Oh!
-[woman pants. grunts]

601
00:28:14.382 --> 00:28:16.301
-[Angie] No.
-[Franklin] No. wait. wait.

602
00:28:16.384 --> 00:28:18.386
[grunts] You get off!
I don't know you.

603
00:28:18.524 --> 00:28:19.801
Nice reversal!

604
00:28:19.939 --> 00:28:21.686
[Angie] Hmm. way to come back.
All right.

605
00:28:21.769 --> 00:28:23.322
-No. You!
-[straining]

606
00:28:23.460 --> 00:28:24.806
Um... All right.

607
00:28:24.944 --> 00:28:26.622
[Franklin] She got that slam.
look at that.

608
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:28.051
[woman] Get off me!

609
00:28:28.534 --> 00:28:32.055
-Uh-oh.
-Yeah. APD.

610
00:28:32.849 --> 00:28:34.816
[rhythmic beeping]

611
00:28:34.954 --> 00:28:38.406
Nurses say she sleeps for 23 hours
a day. hadn't been verbal for weeks.

612
00:28:38.544 --> 00:28:40.398
They're just waiting
for her to let go.

613
00:28:40.511 --> 00:28:42.375
And she hadn't had any visitors.

614
00:28:42.997 --> 00:28:45.046
Well. someone brought her
those chocolates.

615
00:28:52.592 --> 00:28:54.940
[beeping continues]

616
00:28:57.770 --> 00:28:58.944
[door opens]

617
00:28:59.082 --> 00:29:00.324
[Will] Freeze! GBI!

618
00:29:00.842 --> 00:29:02.647
-Reed Hobbs. stop!
-[resident gasps]

619
00:29:04.432 --> 00:29:05.640
[shrieks]

620
00:29:05.778 --> 00:29:06.779
[indistinct chatter]

621
00:29:06.917 --> 00:29:08.436
[residents grunt. scream]

622
00:29:11.611 --> 00:29:13.544
[resident 2 grunts]

623
00:29:16.375 --> 00:29:19.240
-[resident 2 straining] I can't breathe.
-[alarm blaring]

624
00:29:19.378 --> 00:29:22.312
-[all clamor]
-[speaks indistinctly]

625
00:29:22.450 --> 00:29:23.727
[Will] Reed. stop!

626
00:29:23.865 --> 00:29:25.487
[♪ Suspenseful music plays]

627
00:29:33.633 --> 00:29:35.463
Reed. Reed.

628
00:29:35.981 --> 00:29:38.742
Listen. I just...
Okay. easy. easy.

629
00:29:38.880 --> 00:29:41.193
I just wanna talk. okay?

630
00:29:41.710 --> 00:29:44.852
-I don't wanna hurt anyone.
-I know that.

631
00:29:46.715 --> 00:29:50.340
You just wanted to see your
grandmother... [panting] ...one last time

632
00:29:51.444 --> 00:29:52.756
to say goodbye.

633
00:29:52.894 --> 00:29:54.102
Isn't that right?

634
00:29:55.448 --> 00:29:57.594
Look. I know what happened
at the restaurant.

635
00:29:59.073 --> 00:30:01.938
I know James Ulster
killed all those people.

636
00:30:02.076 --> 00:30:04.078
I think you wanted
no part of it.

637
00:30:05.596 --> 00:30:07.219
He loves me.

638
00:30:07.667 --> 00:30:11.361
I know he does.
But he's dangerous. okay?

639
00:30:11.499 --> 00:30:15.434
And he's gonna get you
killed. Reed. I know him.

640
00:30:15.883 --> 00:30:18.195
Let me help you. please.

641
00:30:19.541 --> 00:30:21.095
You're Will. right?

642
00:30:22.717 --> 00:30:24.823
He said you're his son too.

643
00:30:25.754 --> 00:30:26.997
Yes.

644
00:30:28.274 --> 00:30:29.640
You know what that makes us?

645
00:30:30.518 --> 00:30:33.038
-We're brothers?
-That's right.

646
00:30:34.039 --> 00:30:37.076
You can trust me. Reed. okay?

647
00:30:37.663 --> 00:30:41.356
Let's put down the gun.
Let's just talk a little. okay?

648
00:30:42.357 --> 00:30:44.187
Tell me what his plan is.

649
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:47.535
So we can stop him
from hurting anybody else.

650
00:30:49.778 --> 00:30:51.401
I don't wanna do this anymore.

651
00:30:52.989 --> 00:30:54.197
[gunshot]

652
00:30:56.785 --> 00:30:57.994
[gasps]

653
00:30:59.754 --> 00:31:02.205
No. [gasping]

654
00:31:02.826 --> 00:31:03.792
[grunts]

655
00:31:03.931 --> 00:31:06.174
What the hell did you just do?

656
00:31:09.039 --> 00:31:10.972
[siren wails]

657
00:31:11.110 --> 00:31:13.271
-[Amanda] What the hell happened here?
-[Faith] A lot of big feelings.

658
00:31:13.354 --> 00:31:15.238
What happened is.
he just shot our best lead.

659
00:31:15.321 --> 00:31:19.291
No. I took out an escaped murderer
that had a gun pointed at you.

660
00:31:19.429 --> 00:31:20.899
You're not even
supposed to be here. Trent.

661
00:31:20.982 --> 00:31:23.177
Thanks to Sheriff Roussard.
our job's half done.

662
00:31:23.260 --> 00:31:24.489
He had a gun pointed on you?

663
00:31:24.572 --> 00:31:26.279
He was lowering it.
We were talking.

664
00:31:26.401 --> 00:31:27.733
He could have helped us
find Ulster.

665
00:31:27.816 --> 00:31:32.373
I don't care! Okay?
You don't know that kid!

666
00:31:32.511 --> 00:31:34.292
Could've changed his mind
blowing your head off!

667
00:31:34.375 --> 00:31:36.066
-I have zero regrets!
-Really?

668
00:31:36.204 --> 00:31:38.413
You know. every life I've taken
weighs on me.

669
00:31:38.551 --> 00:31:40.691
It's so nice that
you can sleep at night.

670
00:31:40.829 --> 00:31:42.590
This isn't your case. Will!

671
00:31:43.142 --> 00:31:44.958
One of the dead guards'
credit cards pinged

672
00:31:45.041 --> 00:31:46.700
at a car rental agency
in Savannah.

673
00:31:46.835 --> 00:31:49.217
Probably Ulster.
I'm gonna go look into it.

674
00:31:49.735 --> 00:31:51.461
All right.
I'll handle the media.

675
00:31:53.256 --> 00:31:56.052
Go back to the office. Will.
[sighs]

676
00:31:56.190 --> 00:31:58.640
-[police chattering on radio]
-[Will huffs]

677
00:32:03.024 --> 00:32:06.372
Look at him. Can't wait to get
his face in front of a camera.

678
00:32:06.510 --> 00:32:07.822
-[grunts]
-[Faith] Oh!

679
00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:10.066
-Are you okay? Okay. okay.
-Yeah.

680
00:32:10.204 --> 00:32:11.377
I just need to sit.

681
00:32:11.515 --> 00:32:13.517
[Faith] Okay.
All right. easy now.

682
00:32:15.243 --> 00:32:17.452
Great.
This is just what I need.

683
00:32:17.590 --> 00:32:20.593
It's Bill Appleyard watching me
collapse in the street.

684
00:32:20.731 --> 00:32:24.701
Okay. so. what are we gonna do
about this jackass?

685
00:32:25.564 --> 00:32:27.393
-Should we kill him?
-[scoffs]

686
00:32:27.531 --> 00:32:31.363
Guys like that can't be killed.
They just get promoted.

687
00:32:32.812 --> 00:32:35.643
How's Will doin'? Really.

688
00:32:36.333 --> 00:32:38.094
I think
if we don't catch this guy.

689
00:32:38.232 --> 00:32:40.234
then he's gonna go off
the deep end.

690
00:32:41.235 --> 00:32:43.479
And it's not helping
that he's not on the case.

691
00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:46.965
I know. [breathes heavily]

692
00:32:48.138 --> 00:32:50.244
I just can't lose him.

693
00:32:57.458 --> 00:33:00.668
But James. he would
write me these letters.

694
00:33:00.806 --> 00:33:05.569
I mean. long. long letters that
were full of the most romantic things.

695
00:33:05.707 --> 00:33:07.054
I mean. one time...

696
00:33:07.192 --> 00:33:09.214
He told me he wished my eyes
were swimming pools so...

697
00:33:09.297 --> 00:33:13.646
So he could just. boop.
take a dip in my eyes.

698
00:33:13.784 --> 00:33:16.635
Isn't that the most romantic
thing you've ever heard? I know.

699
00:33:16.718 --> 00:33:18.775
I can see how that
would bowl a person over.

700
00:33:18.858 --> 00:33:20.881
Do you have any idea
where he might be going?

701
00:33:20.964 --> 00:33:25.003
He says his last thought before
he drifts off is the smell of my hair.

702
00:33:25.141 --> 00:33:26.418
[sniffs]

703
00:33:26.556 --> 00:33:28.199
He's never even
smelled my hair before.

704
00:33:28.282 --> 00:33:30.477
It's just the thought
of the smell of my hair.

705
00:33:30.560 --> 00:33:32.596
It just holds him in a spell.

706
00:33:32.734 --> 00:33:35.806
He has killed ten people
in the last 48 hours.

707
00:33:35.944 --> 00:33:37.463
Aw. I hope he's okay.

708
00:33:37.601 --> 00:33:39.362
I'm sure he had his reasons.

709
00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:42.468
We know that a courier made
a drop of cash and passports.

710
00:33:42.606 --> 00:33:44.608
Was that you or was that Lisa?

711
00:33:44.746 --> 00:33:48.612
You really think that piece of
trash could come up with ten grand?

712
00:33:48.750 --> 00:33:49.806
Okay. so that was you.

713
00:33:49.889 --> 00:33:52.513
I didn't say that.
Did I say that?

714
00:33:52.651 --> 00:33:54.342
Okay.

715
00:33:54.480 --> 00:33:56.537
I've had enough. You wanna hear
what your fiance has been telling Lisa?

716
00:33:56.620 --> 00:33:58.643
[phone beeps] -[Lisa]
<i>He says his last thought</i>

717
00:33:58.726 --> 00:34:01.453
<i>before he drifts off
is the smell of my hair.</i>

718
00:34:01.591 --> 00:34:02.626
But...

719
00:34:03.455 --> 00:34:07.562
But that was our thing.
That was our thing.

720
00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:10.117
<i>It's just the thought
of the smell of my hair.</i>

721
00:34:10.255 --> 00:34:11.739
<i>It just holds him in a spell.</i>

722
00:34:11.877 --> 00:34:13.154
Oh. that two-timing...

723
00:34:13.292 --> 00:34:15.260
[weeping] Asshole.

724
00:34:16.640 --> 00:34:20.265
[muffled] I love him.
but that was my thing. [cries]

725
00:34:20.403 --> 00:34:23.164
He's never even
smelled her hair.

726
00:34:23.302 --> 00:34:26.202
Well. ours is pissed
and she lawyered up.

727
00:34:26.340 --> 00:34:28.514
Mine's uncontrollably weeping.

728
00:34:29.998 --> 00:34:31.414
Let me take a run at weepy.

729
00:34:31.552 --> 00:34:34.072
-What are you gonna do?
-Don't worry about it.

730
00:34:35.866 --> 00:34:39.180
[Janice-Theresa whimpers]
Thank you.

731
00:34:42.045 --> 00:34:44.841
[♪ "I Will Survive" playing]

732
00:34:44.979 --> 00:34:48.189
[Franklin] October 14th. 2017.

733
00:34:48.327 --> 00:34:49.604
What?

734
00:34:49.742 --> 00:34:53.021
It was a Saturday.
Ruth's Chris Steak House.

735
00:34:53.781 --> 00:34:55.679
I was waiting on
my boyfriend. Jerod.

736
00:34:55.817 --> 00:35:00.063
We were eight months in.
and I was in love.

737
00:35:00.201 --> 00:35:01.616
<i>♪ I grew strong ♪</i>

738
00:35:01.754 --> 00:35:03.811
But then my buddy Charles
texted me a bombshell

739
00:35:03.894 --> 00:35:08.934
that Jerod was married
to a woman with two kids.

740
00:35:09.072 --> 00:35:10.763
-In Marietta.
-Really?

741
00:35:11.212 --> 00:35:12.144
Men are pigs.

742
00:35:12.282 --> 00:35:13.594
I know.

743
00:35:13.732 --> 00:35:15.906
So I see you. Janice-Theresa.

744
00:35:16.044 --> 00:35:19.634
and I want you to know
that you are not alone.

745
00:35:19.772 --> 00:35:22.016
We're all Janice-Theresa Weggle.

746
00:35:22.154 --> 00:35:24.867
So let me tell you something as
one Janice-Theresa to another.

747
00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:28.056
This is not
the end of your story.

748
00:35:28.195 --> 00:35:29.644
-Yeah. it is.
-[sighs]

749
00:35:29.782 --> 00:35:32.992
This is where your story begins.

750
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:37.031
No. It is not. I don't think
I'll ever love again.

751
00:35:37.169 --> 00:35:38.205
<i>♪ No. not I ♪</i>

752
00:35:38.343 --> 00:35:41.518
Yes. you will.

753
00:35:41.656 --> 00:35:43.417
You're gonna come back
from this.

754
00:35:43.555 --> 00:35:45.798
You're gonna rise
from the ashes.

755
00:35:45.936 --> 00:35:49.319
In fact. I'm gonna call you
Janice-Theresa-Phoenix.

756
00:35:49.457 --> 00:35:52.288
Oh. I don't know.
That's a lot of hyphens.

757
00:35:52.426 --> 00:35:56.740
You are worth it. Janice
hyphen Theresa hyphen Phoenix.

758
00:35:56.878 --> 00:35:59.433
She's eating out of
the palm of his hand.

759
00:36:00.744 --> 00:36:03.299
-Is this story true?
-Who cares?

760
00:36:05.818 --> 00:36:07.648
Hey. Now look.
there's only one thing

761
00:36:07.786 --> 00:36:11.962
standing between you and the
sweet revenge of a happy life.

762
00:36:12.100 --> 00:36:14.206
-What?
-You're in a bit of trouble now.

763
00:36:14.344 --> 00:36:17.796
-[weeping] No.
-You have aided and abetted a known felon

764
00:36:17.934 --> 00:36:19.970
who is racking up
quite a body count.

765
00:36:20.108 --> 00:36:21.571
[whispering] Are they gonna...

766
00:36:21.662 --> 00:36:23.167
[normal voice] Are they gonna
give me the chair?

767
00:36:23.250 --> 00:36:25.134
We're gonna do everything
in our power to avoid that.

768
00:36:25.217 --> 00:36:27.274
but I need you to be honest
with me so I can save your life.

769
00:36:27.357 --> 00:36:28.600
Yeah. yeah.

770
00:36:28.738 --> 00:36:31.361
Now. Ulster's had.
like. two fiancees.

771
00:36:31.499 --> 00:36:34.157
Is it possible that
maybe there's a third?

772
00:36:34.295 --> 00:36:35.986
-Maybe even a fourth?
-No. No!

773
00:36:36.124 --> 00:36:39.266
No. it's not possible.
It's just... It's...

774
00:36:39.404 --> 00:36:41.302
Well. there was Jackie.

775
00:36:41.854 --> 00:36:44.409
but they ended things
about a year ago. so...

776
00:36:45.237 --> 00:36:46.721
Who's Jackie?

777
00:36:47.826 --> 00:36:49.276
My sister.

778
00:36:49.724 --> 00:36:52.071
I'm gonna need an address. JTP.

779
00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:54.315
<i>♪ I will survive ♪</i>

780
00:36:56.352 --> 00:36:58.008
[♪ music ends]

781
00:37:07.190 --> 00:37:10.400
Jackie Weggle. Two
gunshot wounds to the chest.

782
00:37:10.538 --> 00:37:12.713
Pete thinks it was less
than two hours ago.

783
00:37:14.024 --> 00:37:15.163
[Will sighs]

784
00:37:15.302 --> 00:37:16.544
Why would he do this?

785
00:37:16.682 --> 00:37:19.340
Well. her car is missing. so...

786
00:37:21.308 --> 00:37:23.965
You're not acting like
you got kicked off the case.

787
00:37:24.103 --> 00:37:27.831
Yeah. well... I had to see.

788
00:37:28.729 --> 00:37:30.972
Now he's killing the women
who helped him.

789
00:37:32.284 --> 00:37:34.217
He's never gonna stop.

790
00:37:34.355 --> 00:37:36.564
Will. you can sit this out.

791
00:37:37.013 --> 00:37:39.084
We got this.
You didn't create this guy.

792
00:37:39.222 --> 00:37:40.430
No.

793
00:37:42.329 --> 00:37:43.985
But he created me.

794
00:37:46.022 --> 00:37:48.680
He put me in that trash can.
He...

795
00:37:49.543 --> 00:37:54.513
This man dictated my whole life
from the moment I was born.

796
00:37:56.550 --> 00:37:57.827
[sighs]

797
00:37:59.415 --> 00:38:00.968
I have to end this.

798
00:38:01.624 --> 00:38:03.453
So you're torturing yourself.

799
00:38:04.868 --> 00:38:05.904
A little bit.

800
00:38:07.906 --> 00:38:12.324
He's. uh... He's in my head.

801
00:38:13.601 --> 00:38:15.465
-Oh.
-[chuckles]

802
00:38:16.880 --> 00:38:18.917
He beating the crap
out of you in there?

803
00:38:23.266 --> 00:38:24.474
Yeah.

804
00:38:37.729 --> 00:38:40.801
By the way. congratulations.

805
00:38:41.249 --> 00:38:42.285
What?

806
00:38:42.423 --> 00:38:44.356
I saw the ring.

807
00:38:45.599 --> 00:38:47.117
Happy for you. Ang.

808
00:39:01.822 --> 00:39:04.259
We have full surveillance
on the rental car agency.

809
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:06.171
Ulster hasn't shown up.

810
00:39:06.309 --> 00:39:08.780
We have flock cameras checking
for Jackie Weggle's Chevy Malibu.

811
00:39:08.863 --> 00:39:10.610
We think that's
what he's driving now.

812
00:39:10.693 --> 00:39:12.626
I have all my men
watching the agency.

813
00:39:12.764 --> 00:39:15.456
and the moment James Ulster
shows up. we'll have him.

814
00:39:18.252 --> 00:39:21.497
[phone buzzes] - [Eduardo]
<i>Unknown number calling.</i>

815
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.120
<i>Unknown number calling.</i>

816
00:39:25.397 --> 00:39:27.192
Trent.

817
00:39:27.330 --> 00:39:30.782
Did you know sharks can hear
their prey from 3.000 feet away?

818
00:39:30.920 --> 00:39:33.371
[♪ "Magic Arrow" playing]

819
00:39:33.509 --> 00:39:35.200
What did you do?

820
00:39:35.338 --> 00:39:39.100
Nothing yet. but if I have
to hear another shark fact...

821
00:39:39.238 --> 00:39:40.999
[Will]
<i>If you hurt that boy. James...</i>

822
00:39:41.137 --> 00:39:43.505
[James] <i>No. Will. you are not
in charge this time.</i>

823
00:39:43.588 --> 00:39:44.934
I am.

824
00:39:46.211 --> 00:39:47.868
[whispering] He took my son.

825
00:39:49.732 --> 00:39:51.147
<i>I'm taking his.</i>

826
00:39:54.426 --> 00:39:56.083
Tell me where to meet you.

827
00:39:58.741 --> 00:40:02.227
<i>♪ Mystic palm
Gem and tarot ♪</i>

828
00:40:02.365 --> 00:40:03.331
Hello. Will.

829
00:40:03.470 --> 00:40:05.057
You can stop right there.

830
00:40:05.851 --> 00:40:08.129
Uncle Will.
we've been waiting for you.

831
00:40:11.995 --> 00:40:15.205
You can put yours...
right here.

832
00:40:16.690 --> 00:40:19.175
Hey. Calvin.
I got a new one for you.

833
00:40:20.728 --> 00:40:24.732
Did you know that sharks can't
get cavities? Isn't that crazy?

834
00:40:24.870 --> 00:40:28.633
Lucky sharks. No dentist.

835
00:40:29.461 --> 00:40:32.395
Hey. you see that family
over there?

836
00:40:32.982 --> 00:40:34.625
I want you to run over to them.
all right?

837
00:40:34.708 --> 00:40:36.675
You're gonna ask
to use their cell phone.

838
00:40:36.813 --> 00:40:40.334
Call this number. ask to speak
to Faith Mitchell. She's my friend.

839
00:40:40.472 --> 00:40:42.612
You tell her you need
to be picked up. okay?

840
00:40:42.750 --> 00:40:44.580
Okay. What are you doing?

841
00:40:44.718 --> 00:40:48.515
I'm gonna hang here and play a
little game with my friend James.

842
00:40:49.101 --> 00:40:52.242
Go ahead. okay?
Your mom's gonna be worried.

843
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:55.556
Well. I'm gonna miss you.

844
00:40:58.525 --> 00:40:59.974
[James] Bye-bye.

845
00:41:01.976 --> 00:41:03.806
Oh. I knew you'd come.

846
00:41:04.600 --> 00:41:06.256
Because deep down...

847
00:41:06.878 --> 00:41:10.709
you know I'm the father
you deserve.

848
00:41:12.711 --> 00:41:14.023
Maybe.

849
00:41:14.161 --> 00:41:18.234
The problem is...
I'm running out of options.

850
00:41:19.477 --> 00:41:22.687
Caleb. cliche though he may be.

851
00:41:22.825 --> 00:41:24.999
is surprisingly good at his job.

852
00:41:35.320 --> 00:41:39.186
You and your cowboy father
will never stop looking for me.

853
00:41:39.324 --> 00:41:43.086
which leaves me
with just one choice.

854
00:41:44.363 --> 00:41:45.917
And what's that?

855
00:41:47.884 --> 00:41:49.092
[gun hammer cocks]

856
00:41:51.888 --> 00:41:54.235
[sighs] It's time to die.

857
00:41:56.893 --> 00:41:59.827
<i>♪ Our mother's milk
Double faro ♪</i>

858
00:41:59.965 --> 00:42:01.470
-[siren blares]
-[Faith] You ready?

859
00:42:01.553 --> 00:42:03.762
All right. Let's go.

860
00:42:04.694 --> 00:42:07.110
It's good to see your family.

861
00:42:08.802 --> 00:42:10.928
-Calvin. you okay?
-[Faith] Yeah. he's okay.

862
00:42:11.011 --> 00:42:13.102
We got to turn on the
police sirens. right. Calvin?

863
00:42:13.185 --> 00:42:14.290
Come here. baby.

864
00:42:15.015 --> 00:42:17.210
-What happened?
-Ulster took him from his day camp

865
00:42:17.293 --> 00:42:22.367
and then. according to Calvin.
Uncle Will traded places with him.

866
00:42:22.747 --> 00:42:23.955
Ulster has Will?

867
00:42:24.472 --> 00:42:26.405
[phone rings]

868
00:42:26.544 --> 00:42:27.752
Roussard.

869
00:42:30.720 --> 00:42:32.066
They found the Malibu.

870
00:42:32.204 --> 00:42:33.274
What?

871
00:42:50.602 --> 00:42:53.985
They found two bodies.
[panting] Is it Will's?

872
00:42:58.714 --> 00:43:01.026
It's not. is it?

873
00:43:02.096 --> 00:43:03.270
It's his.

874
00:43:03.408 --> 00:43:04.789
Oh. my God.

875
00:43:06.514 --> 00:43:07.964
Will.

875
00:43:08.305 --> 00:44:08.616
